article.headline: San Jose St. 68, Weber St. 67
article.story: SAN JOSE, Calif. -- D.J. Brown converted four key free throws in the final minute of overtime and San Jose State slipped past Weber State 68-67 on Thursday night. A basket by Davion Berry with 1:08 left in overtime gave Weber State (1-1) a 67-64 lead, but Brown brought the Spartans (1-2) back with two free throws at the 1:01 and two more with :09 showing. James Kinney scored 24 points to lead San Jose State and Chris Cunningham had 10 points. Davion Berry led Weber State with 21 points and Scott Bamforth scored 11. Joel Bolomboy grabbed 11 rebounds for the Wildcats.
